<br>
Perhaps we need to ask a completely different question:<br>
<br>
1)  Does Verant INTEND that only SOME clerics will have their epic?<br>
<br>
I think the answer is yes.<br>
<br>
Now the question is:  WHO gets their epic and WHO does not.  This depends entirely on us.  All things being equal, those guilds with enough force to take Rage will end up being the guilds that have epic clerics.  That said, some clerics on Rodcet have created a list.  Contrary to some beliefs, this favors the smaller guilds.  They can be at the top of the list someday, and CLIAM rights, theoretically precluding the mighty from simply taking it.<br>
<br>
I don't agree with the list as it stands.  It is a scheme wherein all the clerics that will ever get their epic are on the front of the list - and noone else would ever get it.  The current waiting list is over a year.<br>
<br>
I also don't think Verant HAS to fix anything.  If they only want some clerics to be epic, so be it.<br>
<br>
So... what to do?  I think rage needs to be set back to what every other mob is... you get there first, you camp, you agro.  If someone adds too much structure to the &quot;who is next up on the hill&quot; then FFA will, and HAS TO happen.  A list can only work if supply will equal demand in a timely fashion.  That is not the case.  Plain and simple, only some clerics can have their EPIC as it is programmed today.  Let that be governed like any other MOB.<br>
<br>
This is a change in my personal opinion, but I have listened to both sides and I have concluded that the list is disfunctional, and can never win support server wide. <p><b><i><font face="Garamond"><font color="#993366"><font size=+2>
