<br>
First off, I just want to say that I do not support the list, I never have. But, I have always respected it and I intend to do so. I have helped a few people kill Ragefire and I will continue to do so if needed/asked.<br>
Also, these views are my own, not the official stance of my guild (Cascade Point). The stance of my guild is it's own and should not included in any way in this post.<br>
<br>
The biggest flaw I see with the list is that the people who benefited from it most were the people who created it. Those are the people who have their epic now. People who chased others away from SF because they were 'not on the list' although they didn't even know about it. So the list was something that a small part of Rodcet forced others to tag along on. If the list was to have been made fairly then every single cleric on Rodcet should have been asked if they agreed on it. And, if the answer was yes, then everyone should have been in a lotto to see who got the first shot at Rage. This is the first fatal flaw in the list.<br>
Second, the list cannot work with the number of people that are on it. EQ wont be around long enough for all these people to get their epic. There just isn't time. And anyone making a cleric today would not have a prayer to get their epic ever, if everyone should follow the list. Of course, VI (Verant Interactive) takes a major share of blame in this since they wont allow everyone who wants to, to get an epic. This is true about all the epics, the cleric one is just the one who most people want to get and it cannot be done.<br>
Take the rogue epic for instance. It 'could' be possible for 500 people to complete it in a row. All you need to do is to spawn the general often enough. You can't do that with Ragefire.<br>
Ragefire just doesn't support any kind of list system as it will always be unfair to someone. But then again, FFA (free for all) doesn't work either since that will also be unfair to a lot of people. FFA will work best for the cleric who has 5 manaburn wizards and thus gets killshot. <br>
The only way to make the cleric epic any fair is to change it so that more people have access to it, a thing which VI has said they will not do.<br>
As I see it there is no 'right' way to deal with Ragefire and the cleric epic at the moment. It just can't be done. What ever people try to do someone will be against it. We are just too different to be able to agree on a matter like this. Of course, this difference is the same that makes so many of us enjoy this world of Norrath, it is what drives us to find new friends and new adventures and why we keep coming back. <br>
<br>
But in the end I hope that we can all at least agree on one thing... Ragefire sucks in a quite majorly way indeed.<br>
